originalText.text: My first 5 months at 555Ten have been good. In looking for my apartment I wanted reasonable space, good natural light, in-unit laundry facilities and SAFETY. The staff - including doormen, maintenance team, cleaning staff - are courteous and professional. I've found management responsive. I agree with others comments that not all the amenities opened on time, but I'm a working professional so pool(s) weren't high on my priority list. Can't comment about the dog run, as I'm not a pet owner. The dog run hours were curbed to allow quiet during Sunday morning church services next store - seems like a reasonable request to me.  We are still under construction on my floor, but the workers don't start before 7:30 am and are gone by 5. Could management communication of upcoming changes (ie hot water being off for maintenance etc) be better?  Sure.  Is it terrible? No. I'll be watching as the new buildings come online in Hudson Yards to see if there is any price competition, but for now I'm very happy here.

originalText.text: After touring the building, I reached out to agent J for information on updated availability, given the discrepancies on their website. However, my attempts to get answers were met with resounding silence. Despite a follow-up email, copying the building leasing email, a new contact, Y, responded but failed to address my question and then disappeared. If they can't be bothered to respond to a prospective resident, I strongly recommend you explore other rental options. These folks lack the basic courtesy and professionalism necessary to assist you in your search.

originalText.text: the only reason people give anything above 1 star is because they’ve been fortunate enough to not require management’s help for anything. or they have infinite patience. the people in the management office do not care about you as a tenant, nor as a person. don’t think for a second that your inconveniences caused by things constantly going wrong in the building matter to them. you’ll be sorely disappointed, business is business, sure, it just really sucks to call this home. the building staff is really great, i’ll continue tipping them generously during the holidays because they really deserve it. but this place has lost its charm and management couldn’t care less, really not worth it.

originalText.text: This is the worst building I have ever lived in. I would NOT recommend moving here. I live next to and below the units that the crane smashed into. They moved out all units around and above me out. They refuse to give me a discount in rent, relocate me to another apartment or break my lease. Some of the amenities are closed and the elevators are never working. Property Manager with Extell Jennifer Mercedes and Naim have been extremely rude and unhelpful. I work from home and the noise is ridiculous. I hear noise above and to the side of me all day. DO NOT MOVE HERE
